Apple Blames iPhone 'Touch Disease' on Clumsy Users posted by Michael Harthorne, Newser Staff - Just now share 
While they aren't exploding like a certain other smartphone , Apple's iPhone 6s and 6 Pluses have come down with what iFixit calls Touch Disease . As PC World reports, Touch Disease manifests as a flickering gray bar and nonfunctional touchscreen. { "position1" : { "type" : "live", "id" : 6043, "name" : "NBC News Radio", "description" : "The news you want, when you want it" } } 
Phones get Touch Disease "after being dropped multiple times on a hard surface and then incurring further stress on the device," according to Apple , which is offering to fix the problem‚Äîin iPhone 6 Pluses anyway‚Äîfor $149. But a source at Apple Genius tells iFixit they aren't actually repairing the broken phones, just replacing them with refurbished ones. And iFixit notes that's "a lot of money for [a] device swap."
